text: That is rough. On the plus side, if you did get it while wearing a mask it greatly reduces your chances of having a severe case, as the viral load would be low. Good luck!! I hope you feel better quickly!! I'm 99% certain I had it in January. The frustrating thing was that I'd start to feel better, and then the next day I'd feel worse—a bit of a rollercoaster. It took me about three weeks to feel like myself. I had the weird toe thing, too, where they looked like I had stubbed a few toes and got blisters. (That was the strangest thing.) My partner had it right before me and he would cough so badly he'd puke. He still has a cough like an allergy cough each morning, and it took him a few months to get his lung capacity back up. Neither of us tested positive for the flu, and there weren't Covid tests back then because it wasn't supposed to be in the US (now they know it was here in early December). We need to have antibody tests done, but are living as if we haven't had it. I will be floored if it wasn't Covid, though. And good luck!! Hope it's just a small bug.
